In case you missed it, here are the top News stories of the week: 1. DROWNED WHILE DOING RITUALS! The community of Eerterus F4 near Stinkwater in Hammanskraal is reeling in shock after five men believed to be ZCC church members were swept away in a dam in the area. 2. 4 LEGGED CREATURE LEAVES RESIDENTS IN FEAR! A crocodile was seen near the spot where kids cross the river to go to school but so far, it hasn't been caught. 3. LIFE GOES ON FOR ZULU KING! Despite facing court challenges and a dispute over the throne, King Misuzulu is continuing with his duties. 4. CAR CLEANSING ENDS IN HORROR! Two men visited Pastor Mzwakhe Mfene on Sunday, 16 January and asked him to cleanse their car. 5. KARATE 'FIGHTING' COP VIDEO GOES VIRAL! A video that is circulating on social media of a cop attacking other officers in Mitchells Plain, Cape Town, has left many people shocked.